metadata.name: fx(ornament) 2022 #1830
metadata.description:
Tis the season to celebrate and what better way than with a collectible series of 2022 generative ornaments. Perfect for yourself or as gifts for people you love. 

Designed to be printed or plotted and then cut out and hung on your tree or any other place that needs a little festive cheer. 

I‚Äôll be picking a few of my favorite outputs and sending the token owners special limited edition signed laser cut versions of their ornaments. 

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

LIVE MODE FEATURES
- L prepares it for plotting or cutting
- S exports a layered SVG
- P exports a PNG
- 1-9 plays with color combos

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

For years my family has collected Wallace Silver Candy Cane ornaments. Each Christmas the kids open up that years design and add it to the tree. With my daughters mostly grown, we now have quite the collection of dozens of ornaments from all the years. Each one full with memories and emotions. 

This series is inspired by that tradition, starting with 2022, and continuing with a new release each year. I hope you enjoy this series and it brings much delight and joy to you, your family, and friends this holiday season.

metadata.name: Off the grid V.2 #221
metadata.description:
Vanilla JS + SVG
January 2022

Edition of 512

"Off the grid" is my attempt to bring human imperfection to the strict formality of a generative grid-based piece.

Grid-plotted geometric forms are very slightly offset, rotated out of position by a degree or two, or absented entirely from the grid. The number of passes is dictated by the hash, and the results will vary from minimal (4 passes) to maximal (13 passes). The sizes of the forms can vary or be all the same, leading to quite different outputs, further emphasized by the different 'canvas' sizes.

The features are:
Format (Portrait, Landscape or Square), Palette (10 in total), Coverage (Full or Indented), Passes (the number of times the algorithm makes a grid) and Sizes (the sizes of the shapes in the grid, Single [one size] or Multiple).

'S' saves an SVG
'P' saves a PNG

[Please note this project will display, but will not work as intended on most IOS devices]

metadata.description:
This is sort of a combo of two of my previous pieces that I have released on fxhash. There are 11 different potential color palettes that are randomly chosen to make up each generative art piece. Note that it may take a little bit for the image to render. This project is best enjoyed in full screen mode. Hope you enjoy!

Created with p5js.
